data.content:
Here's the minimal program (`Program.cs`):

```csharp
using System.Text.Json;

var person = new Person("Jane", 30);
var json = JsonSerializer.Serialize(person, new JsonSerializerOptions { PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase });
Console.WriteLine(json);

public record Person(string Name, int Age);
```

Output: `{"name":"Jane","age":30}`

The key is `JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase` passed via `JsonSerializerOptions` — it converts PascalCase properties (`Name`, `Age`) to camelCase (`name`, `age`). No extra NuGet packages needed; `System.Text.Json` is built into .NET 8.
